Task 3 – Coding & Collaboration Platforms
In this task, I used coding platforms as well as collaboration platforms.

Firstly, I completed a beginner-level coding problem on HackerRank, which helped me understand coding practice platforms. 
Secondly, I designed a Google Form with the title 'Digital Literacy Awareness Quiz,' consisting of five questions, and then linked it with a response sheet.

Digital Literacy Tools and Learning Experience

For this task, I used Google Forms and Google Sheets to design and manage a Digital Literacy Awareness Quiz. Google Forms allowed me to create structured questions including multiple choice, short answer, and checkbox types, while also enabling automatic response collection. 
I explored features like answer validation, quiz mode, and response summaries. The integration with Google Sheets helped in organizing and analyzing the collected data efficiently.

Through this activity, I practised creating surveys, designing user-friendly forms, and understanding how digital tools can be used for data collection and awareness initiatives.
I also learned how to share forms securely and interpret response analytics.

These tools will be highly beneficial academically as they can be used for conducting surveys, collecting research data, organizing feedback, and collaborating on projects. Overall,
this task improved my practical knowledge of digital platforms and strengthened my understanding of responsible and effective digital usage.
